topicSummary: Earwax is a normal physiological substance which is a combination of dead flattened cells, cerumen (a wax-like substance), sebum

latestChanges.title: Reviewed
latestChanges.body: A literature search was conducted in July 2016 to identify evidence-based guidelines, UK policy, systematic reviews, and key RCTs published since the last revision of the topic. No changes to clinical recommendations have been made.
